        public static String[] extractCredentialsFromAuthzHeader(String authorizationHeader)
                                                  throws org.wso2.carbon.identity.oauth.common.exception.OAuthClientException
        Extracts the username and password info from the HTTP Authorization Header
        Parameters:
        authorizationHeader - "Basic " + base64encode(username + ":" + password)
        Returns:
        String array with client id and client secret.
        Throws:
        org.wso2.carbon.identity.oauth.common.exception.OAuthClientException - If the decoded data is null.

        errorMessage - : Error Message

      • getErrorPageURL

        public static String getErrorPageURL(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                     String errorCode,
                                     String errorMessage,
                                     String appName)
        Returns the error page URL. If appName is not null it will be added as query parameter to be displayed to the user. If redirect_uri is null the common error page URL will be returned. If sp name and tenant domain available in the request (as a parameter or using the referer header) those will be added as query params.
        Parameters:
        request - HttpServletRequest
        errorCode - Error Code.
        errorMessage - Error Message.
        appName - Application Name.
        Returns:
        redirect error page url.

      • getErrorPageURL

        public static String getErrorPageURL(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                     String errorCode,
                                     String subErrorCode,
                                     String errorMessage,
                                     String appName)
        Returns the error page URL. If RedirectToRequestedRedirectUri property is true and if the resource owner denies the access request or if the request fails for reasons other than a missing or invalid redirection URI, the authorization server informs the client by adding the error code, error message and state parameters to the query component of the redirection URI.

        If RedirectToRequestedRedirectUri property is false OR if the request fails due to a missing, invalid, or mismatching redirection URI, or if the client identifier is missing or invalid, the authorization server SHOULD inform the resource owner of the error and MUST NOT automatically redirect the user-agent to the invalid redirection URI.

        Parameters:
        request - HttpServletRequest
        errorCode - Error Code
        subErrorCode - Sub error code to identify the exact reason for invalid request
        errorMessage - Message of the error
        appName - Application Name
        Returns:
        url of the redirect error page
